Key Match Events: Pakistan booked their place in the final with a seven-wicket win over New Zealand.
Shaheen Shah Afridi took two wickets for 24 runs in his four overs.
Devon Conway was run out by a direct hit from Shadab Khan.
Daryl Mitchell scored an unbeaten 53 off 35 balls.
Shan Masood scored the winning run.
Post-Match Reflections: Kane Williamson acknowledged Pakistan's superior performance and expressed disappointment in New Zealand's fielding.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the 12th time New Zealand reached the final four of a global tournament but they have yet to lift a trophy.
